parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The deformation or loosening of the fuel tank can cause it to become detached from the motorcycle in the event of an accident, leading to a potential fire hazard, serious injury, or even death.
symptoms: The fuel tank appears deformed or warped
the tank moves or wobbles excessively
the tank is no longer secured by its brackets
the tank is held in place only by a single rear bolt
the tank lifts off the bike due to warping.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Gas Tank Expansion and Support Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The expansion of the gas tank can cause it to become unsupported, leading to a potential fuel leak, fire hazard, or loss of control, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The gas tank has expanded and spread wider than the supports on either side of the motorcycle
the fuel hose from the pump to the filter is faulty and has shrunk
restricted fuel flow to the engine.
